# Structure & layering

- `routes/`: wire HTTP → controller + middlewares (no business logic)
- `controllers/`: parse inputs, call service, shape HTTP response
- `services/`: business rules and orchestration
- `repos/` (or `repositories/`): data access only
- `middlewares/`, `validators/`, `utils/`: focused, not catch-all

Rules:
- Controllers must not do direct DB queries; call service/repo.
- Repos must not depend on Express (`req/res/next`).
